getCp

public java.util.List getCp()
Gets the value of the Cp property. This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the Cp property. For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 
    getCp().add(newItem);
